http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/%E2%80%98Adibhatla-Aaradanotsavalu%E2%80%99-begins-at-Vizianagaram/article14024158.ece

On the occasion of the 71{+s}{+t}anniversary of Harikatha exponent Adibhatla Narayana Das, Sri Adibhatla Sri Kala Peetham, in association with the Department of Culture, is organising a three-day Adibhatla Narayana Das Aarandanotsavalu beginning Wednesday. Assistant Director ( I & PR) K. Jaya Rao, Kala Peetham founder president P. Kalyani and noted litterateur Manapragada Sesha Sai inaugurated the Aarandanotsavalu.Mr. Sesha Sai said Adibhatla was the first principal of the Maharajah’s Sanskrit College, and that he would be remembered for ever for pioneering Harikatha and taking it to the height of excellence.Bhagavatarini Kalyani said that her love for Harikatha made her perform non-stop for 108 hours which earned her a place in Limca Book of Records .Earlier, a rally to mark beginning of the Aaradanotsavalu was taken out from Sri Adibhatla’s house at Kanugantivari Street in the fort town to the venue.Later, rendition of Harikathas - Sita Kalyanam, Karna, Bhakta Ambareesha Katha and Gajendra Moksham by Bhagavatarini K. Kalyani of Anakapalle, K. Narayana Bhagavatar of Visakhapatnam, Bhagavatarini S. Bharati of Eluru, and Dhulipala Sivaramakrishna Bhagavatar of Guntur - respectively enthralled the audience.Thursday’s programmeParvathi Kalyanam Harikatha by Adibhatla Ravi Bhagavatar of Vizianagaram from 10.30 a.m. to 11.30 a.m.; Sathi Sakku Bai by Bhagavatarini P. Janaki Devi from 11.30 a.m. to 12.30 p.m.; Paduka Pattabhishekam by B. Ranga Rao Bhagavatar of Srikakulam from 12.30 p.m. to 1 p.m.; Ahalya Sepa Vimochanam by Padala Rama Dasu Bhagavatar of Hyderabad from 4 p.m. to 6 p.m.; Sri Rama-Sugriva Maitri by Puranam Vijayalakshmi from 6 p.m. to 7 p.m. and Sri Krishna Mahima by Mudapaka Bala Sundaram of Tadepalligudem from 8 p.m. to 10 p.m.